OL,5, Nearly 400,000 self-employed people on 
OL,6, low incomes are being penalised for    
OL,7, filing their tax returns late when most
OL,8, of them don't owe any tax.             
OL,10,FPenalties can build up until people owe
OL,11,Fthousands of pounds, according to Tax  
OL,12,FPolicy Associates.                     
OL,14,FThe non-profit called for penalties to 
OL,15,Fbe cancelled if HMRC finds people have 
OL,16,Fno taxable income.                     
OL,18,FHMRC said new rules would mean people  
OL,19,Fwho sometimes miss a filing deadline   
OL,20,Fwould not be penalised.                
